    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Mothers Can't Win</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Margaret Price says Apr 5 articles on mothers and motherhood said nothing about lesbian mothers (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was surprised to find no article on lesbian mothers. I know several couples with babies, and several more who are currently trying to get pregnant.</p>
        <p>Manifestations of this trend are easy to spot -- the well-known (and much-parodied) book ''Heather Has Two Mommies,'' Melissa Etheridge's recent motherhood and even the bibs available in baby stores bearing slogans like ''Hatched by Two Chicks!''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>I was surprised to find no article on lesbian mothers. I know several couples with babies, and several more who are currently trying to get pregnant.</p>
        <p>Manifestations of this trend are easy to spot -- the well-known (and much-parodied) book ''Heather Has Two Mommies,'' Melissa Etheridge's recent motherhood and even the bibs available in baby stores bearing slogans like ''Hatched by Two Chicks!''</p>
        <p>Lesbian mothering raises a host of interesting questions. I hope your magazine will acknowledge and perhaps explore this cohort of mothers sometime.</p>
        <p>Margaret Price  Ann Arbor, Mich.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
